      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Distinct weak layers in the old snowpack necessitate caution. Weak layers in the lower part of the snowpack can be released even by individual winter sport participants in particular at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack, when entering gullies and bowls for example. This applies in particular on northeast, north and northwest facing slopes above the tree line. The avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack and reach medium size. On steep shady slopes the avalanche prone locations are more prevalent. The natural activity of avalanches will gradually increase.",
